subSubSection.paragraph:
Collophore (
Fig. 18A
). Anterior side with about 36–37 ciliate chaetae, 4 elongated lateral mes, 10 mes and 18 mic thin widely distributed on tube, and 4–5 distal chaetae finely ciliate, 2 robust mac, 1 mac slightly smaller, and 1–2 mes; posterior side with about 60 ciliate chaetae (5 unpaired), 1 larger median mac, 10 elongated mes and 46 mic thin (5 unpaired) and widely distributed, distally 3 ciliate chaetae, no smooth chaetae; lateral flap with about 14 chaetae, 7 smooth and 7 ciliate.

